text:
Are Kuldeeep
Kaafi live aadmi ho bhai. Campus laut ke ek koi addition hua hai to tum hi hoge. Baaki to jinse naata tha unke saath hi ghumte the. Naa chahte hue bhi iska shrey Shrey ko.de deta hun. 
Yaadein to tumne exhaustive form mei likh di bhai. Kuch mere liye bhi chhod diye hote. Mai yaha wo likh ke vida leta hu jo mujhe samajh mei aya.
Alag level per mehnati lagte ho bhai. Chehre maano khud iska nazeer ho. Bahut hi mauko per unlucky bhi rhe ho. Per har baar mehnat badhai hi hai. Ye ek foolproof tareeka hai bhai zindagi ka. Kuch bhi ho jae apni mehnat se tum zameen samtal ker hi loge. 
Zimmedariyon ka bojh bhi lagta hai tum per. Use tum khud ulajhne aur suljhane mei saksham ho. Mai to yahi kahunga ki sabke beech apne liye samay zarur nikalna. Khud ko bhi reward ker lena. 
Baaki rangeen to ho hi. Badhiya zindagi guzaar loge.
Best wishes bhai!
author: Manish Chandra Yadav

text:
MSE chhodne ke liye kabhi maaf nahi karunga. 
Sometimes I envy you for the state of chillness you have acquired in your pursuits. This also reminds me of the multiple discussions we have had around this with you sitting in the canteen. Haa it was you because jab bhi kabhi mai jata tha to tum pehle se waha milte the 2 samosa khate hue. Huge shoutout for not paying for the second one. On the face I had to be the canteen secy and oppose it just because I did not have the privilege to do so. 'Corruption allegations' you see. But you had that privilege. Another reason to turn envious. 
ENG437 was fun. I enjoyed reading your answers. Wish I could have read more of your writing. However I doubt if you ever wrote something just for the sake of writing. I like your style. Maybe if you would write more by breaching your chillness accord:/.
Alright I'll take your leave, unlike canteen I can't come back here to find you again. That's how things are in the end.
Given your state of 'chill' , I suppose it would have to be me who has to make efforts to reach out post college. Never mind I'll do so. However genuine efforts from your side would make it smooth. 
Take care dost! Khush rahi zindagi mei
Bye!
author: Manish Chandra Yadav

text:
If you were ever wondering why I hadn't written a memoir up until now, that was because I felt nothing I articulate would be worthy of expressing the admiration & gratitude carried for you, let's give it a try nonetheless ( Yes, another thing of mine you would find silly :p)

You are amongst the 2-3 people on campus who have had the biggest share in shaping and getting me out of the stubborn mindset I came in with. (It was a failure on my part for not being able to express why I was the way I was)
Well, this isn't an implication that I agreed with everything you said but it has certainly refined my thoughts and given a better & more inclusive perspective about the stuff I knew, still sticking with my ideology.

I have seen how hard you try to have a discourse, trying to make people think on a higher note, trying to ensure the wing has enough 'fun' and 'noobs' not refraining from trying out new stuff (ü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è). Like Kuch sabse best work ethics & managerial skills hein tumhare, nothing less than inspiring.
Occasionally resents rahe hein with you for treating me like a child, haha but thanks mumma for always being there , at some of the toughest phases I went through. Rest assured, ab Kabhi ambulance mein bhejne ki zarurat nhi padegi mujhe. (hopefully!)

Kaafi lamba ho Gaya hai already, (see I told this at the start only ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è) wrap up karte hein. Mujhe pta hai tum unn logo mein se rehne waale ho who would go on to being the nearest to their life goals and kaafi lambi list rahegi of the people you interact with, but hope Kar rha hu ki Kabhi randomly campus Ka khayal Aaye toh mind mein CC ke trips, CCD ke Mocha, wing ki baaton aur Kabhi na bhulane waale jazbaato se yaad zaroor aaega ki mujh jaise kisi Bande se interact kiya tha.

Do great things, until next time ü§ù

text:
Hi Sandeep.  
Thanks for being a part of my IIT K journey.  I recall that we had first connected in the second year when we were allotted a common alumni buddy in the Alumni Buddy program. Although my alumni buddy did not connect with me, I am fortunate that I connected with you. 

We have completed numerous courses and course projects together for the last 1 year. I am fortunate that one of the term papers with you resulted in a publication [1] that was also our first conference paper.  You have influenced many of my decisions in the last year that helped me shape my academic interests and future plans.  I hope that our paths will cross again and we collaborate on some research problems at the intersection of our research interests.

All the best for your future endeavors.

[1]Spectral Efficiency in Poisson Cluster Based HetNets with Users-Basestations Correlation https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9342826

text:
Aaj likhne ka kaafi mood bana hai, to thoda lamba or senti jaayega, padhke to tune khush hi hona hai madarchod, tu hi bolti hai naa jyada expressive nahi hu me, pehli or aakhiri baar express kr rhi, to khush ho jaana pdhke, iske baad nhi hone waala ye. One of the best things jo IITK ne mjhe diya hai wo tu hai (sounding like Nareda I know, but chill hai). Yaad hoga tjhe kaisi masoom si, bholi bhaali aayi thi me, mjhe jo itna frank kiya hai logo se, sikhaya ki dost duniya itni achi nhi hai jitni tum samajhti ho, duniya madarchod hai. Har ek cheez me mjhe support kiya, rules todhne sikhaye (sbse epic ESC201 tha), mere itne jyada saare randi rone sune har time, gaaliyan bhi di hai sunne ke baad, but har cheez ka solution nikal jaata tha yrr tjhse baat krke. Ek point tha meri har problem ka solution tu thi, fir ek point aaya (pata hi hoga kyu aaya), jab , meri sbse badi problem hi tu thi. Behenchod, agar kisi insaan ki wajah se me zindagi me kabhi royi hungi naa to wo tu hai. Behechod, bolti hai ki JD or tum ekdum similar ho, to ye nhi samajh aaya tjhe ki wo rota hai itna, to ho sakta hai me bhi roti hu. Mtlb me close nhi hoti logon se jyada, pata hi hai tjhe, but pata nhi terese hu. Wahan Shimla me literally meri feelings ye thi ki yaar sahi me bohot sahi tha pehle ki kisise bhi close nhi thi, kyuki end me to sbko chhodna hi hota hai, ye bhi chhod hi di naa (firse Nareda waali feel). But thike, mtlb mjhe pata hai me tere liye kaafi important hu, but bc banda aane ke baad sab badal jaate hai, tum bhi koi exception nhi thi. Or agar campus me mjhe sbse jyada nafrat ek insaan se hai to wo hai JD, but baat ye hai ki uski jyada koi glti nhi hai usme. Shimla waali trip bohot hi jyada bekaar thi, wahan pe pata nhi hoga 2 raat me bhi kaafi royi thi, but hamesha ki tarah tu thi nhi sambhalne ko, kyuki pati bhi tha naa tumhare paas to, or fir uske baad jab time bacha to tumne Karan ko pakad liya, jisse hume realise hua ki tumhare liye life me aage badhna or doosre log dhoondna bohot aasan hai (another instance jab tune abhi campus me kaha tha ki me nhi aa rhi hall, mjhe hall-9 me patte khelne me bohot majja aa rha hai), but JD or mere jaise logo ke liye nhi hai, yaad rakhna isse. Khair, dost shukriya humare jeevan me aane ke liye, humko sudharne ke liye, Tindal jaise logon ko judge krne me humari help krne ke liye, or hume humare ye upar likhe hue jaise faaltu ke randi rone sunke unko suljhaane ke liye. Me jaanti hu bohot saare logon ko campus me, but dil ka connect sirf tere saath hai, chuhiya, Thanya kisike saath nhi hai. Itni connected bachpan se aaj tak apne gharwaalo ke alawa shayad nhi hongi kisise bhi. Lekin behenchod isiliye connect nhi hoti me, kyuki fir uss insaan se related faaltu ki baaton pe bohot jyada sochne lag jaati hu me, or ye khaaali hone ka asar nhi hai agar tjhe wo lag raha hai to. Agar me bohot jyada hi busy hoti naa to bhi mjhe tere ye last 1 mahine ke ignorance se shayad utna hi farak padta. Bas bhadas thi nikaal di, feel mat krna jyada warna ro dogi. Achi insaan ho yrr tum, bas exclusice raho humare liye, sbke paas jaa jaake unki dikkatein naa suljhaya karo, I feel jealous (ye nhi btaya maine shayad tjhe kabhi pehle). PLease meri life se jaana mat kabhi bhi. Baaki to me nhi jaane dungi, bas JD ki baat aati hai to me fir piche ho jaati hu. Wahan tjhe hi sambhalna pdega. BC pdhte pdhte gaaliyan de rhi hogi ki ek rone waala kam tha kya jo isne bhi shuru kr diye, but thike mummy se nhi royenge to kisse royenge, or hum thodi roj roj rote hai. 

BC bas visible mat krna isko, acha sa gaaliyon bhara likhenge tumhara visible karane le liye.
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
PR calling Festi!!
Yaar teri first memory naa 1st year ki hai, jab tu Katiyar ke liye birthday card banane GH ayaa tha, lol (Am I allowed to openly say this?). Hamesha ye discussion kaafi hota tha humara ki kaafi similar ho tum dono, literal bhai lagte ho. 
Anyway, uske baad Antaragni'19 ke baad ig diwali ke baad call aata hai tera, bro milna hai kuch gadbad ho gyi. BC bhand hoke chhoti ko bata diya tha tune, meri fati nhi thi, but jis tareeke se tu express kr rha tha, aisa lag rha tha ki fatni chahiye. Uske baad to yrr fir CORE TEAM, alag feels, alag expectations, or kaafi jyada enthu. Enthu to ussi se yaad aata hai jo "KAIROS" naam pe kitna jyada discussion hua tha, lol. But, ek point aane ke baad, enthu kaafi down ho gaya tha. Tune or Shrey ne hi milke sambhala tha poora, placements ke baad sbko jinda kiya, or fir karali BC (wo feel nhi hai, but apni Antargni thi yrr). Bohot jyada miss kiya maine, jo hall-12 me saath milke kaam or bakchodi ki hai tum logo ne (photos or videos aa rhi thi mere paas regularly), or jo final night bhand hue ho tum log. Goa trip jldi plan karo yrr, saath me bhand hona hai BC (OAT ki tarah nhi hopefully).  Dukh kaafi raehga on-ground Antaragni naa hone ka, jitna expected tha utni bond nhi ho paayi me team me, but at the end kya hi kar sakte hai.  Khair kaafi BT hai meri udhar, Tindal ke saamne nahi nikali kabhi, tere saamne pata nhi kyu nikal rhi. Anyways, umeed hai Goa me jld hi milenge. Tab tak Take Care, or apna enthu or feel humesha aisi hi rakhna!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

Sabse pehle to uss din Delhi me mere saath ghoomne ke liye THANK YOU!! Uss science museum me kaafi majja aaya tha. Secondly as a person I like you a lot. Kaafi khulke baatein krta hai tu. But here is to hoping we may meet someday, somewhere. And all your dreams and fantasies about physics come true some day. Also, tu bohot awesome hai yrr!! Take Care!!

text:
Yo Ratnesh!!
Yaar sabse pehle to sorry agar meri kisi bhi baat ka kabhi bura laga ho to, dil me kuch nhi hota yrr, bas nikal jaata hai kabhi kabhi pressure or frustation me. Baaki yaar kaafi dedicated or sincere insaan ho tum, or apni responsibilities kaafi ache se poori krte rhe ho hamesha se saari. Majja aaya tha saath kaam krke kaafi, bas ek photo miss ho gyi Antaragni ke time ki, memory rehti hamesha ki wo. Anyway, thanks for being such a supportive and hard-working co-manager. Fir milenge kabhi. All the very best for your future. Take Care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yaar samajh nhi aa rha kya hi likhu tere baare me, ajeeb sa praani hai tu bohot jyada, but dil ke bohot kareeb hai. Bohot jyada hi frequently baat nhi hoti terese, lekin pata rehta hai ki tu hai, or humesha rahega. Kyu hai, wo nhi pata bas, hehe. Gussa aaya tha terepe, jab maal jugaadne ko kaha tha tjhe, or naatak kr rha tha tu, but fir Apollo ke bahar jab reason bataya tha, tab bohot acha laga tha. Wo sunke laga B-115 me start me aake bhi faayda kuch nhi hota XD. Lekin ek baar to aaungi tere paas bhand hoke, tjhe disappoint krne ke liye. 
Purani yaadein to kya hi yaad krni, chhodo, pata hi hai tjhe sab. Baaki wo raakhi ka din yaad rahega mjhe humesha. Pehli baar tjhe legit bhand dekha tha, or gussa nhi aaya tha, kaafi achi harkatein ki thi tune uss din, kulfi khaake. Kaafi fun tha wo, tere mast se expressions, aaj bhi video dekhke majja aa jaata hai. 
Baaki mood swings bade khatarnak hai tere, or fattu to hai hi tu, ab to maan hi jaa. Bas BT padwaani aati hai tjhe, uske baad sambhalna bhi seekhle. 
Chalo UPSC nikalo fatafat, hum bhi faayda uthaye taaki bhai ke sarkari babu hone ka. Milte to rehna hi hai terese. Ache se padhai likhayi karo, or mera naam roshan karo. Take Care!!

text:
1st year me to mujhe tu bada rude sa lagta tha par jabse summer me hmmne mini militia khelna start kiya ishu ke bhaiyon ke saath....aur tumhe janne ka mauka mila tab pata chala ki bada caring hai tu aur witty bhi(tumhare chakkar me mera humour level bhi grow hua haiüòç)üòÅ.  I admire the confidence and intellect you have. Bahut kuch seekha hai tumse aur maze bhi bahut kiye hain apan ne to. Ek baat bata dun exam me mere bagal me cheating karne ka experience tere saath best tha..tu turant samajh jaata tha mai kya kahna chah rha aur kya karne se cheating me asani hogi..tere jaisa koi nhi mila. 
Tumhari baat karna akela incomplete sa lagega isliye pure grp ki memories saath me likh deta hun. 1st year ke baad to "apne launde- mai, tu, pawan, ishu, pankaj aur amit(ekmattr BS walaüòÇüòÇ)" to inseparable se ho gye the. Tumlog mere liye bahut special ho..har cheez share kar skta hun tumlogon ke saath. College ke maximum memories tumlogon ke saath hi kiya hai. Exams me saath padha, apna saara assignment saath me chhapna (aur kitna ladai karte the mai aur nikhil ki kon submit karne jaayega aur agle hi pal phir sab bhul ke canteen me kab khane chale jaate the pata hi nhi chlta tha aur assignment bhi koi aur hi jama karke aata thaüòÇüòÇ), hamara exam me saath me padhna aur ek dusre ko padhana aur phir pata nhi kahan kahan chit likh ke jaana, labs me fraud maarna aur last time pe attendance lagana, raat bhar cricket khelna, amit ki gaand maarna , hamara pehla g***ja experience, H12 PL khelna, mera,ishu  aur nikhil ka pure summer pubg khelna, sabka gym jaana, chitrakut me bhand hone ki wajah se subah prof ko late karwana aur phir bhi na jaanaüòÇüòÇ, amit ki gaand maarna, wing phatta khelna, trip pe jaana, nikhil ka geodesy wale prof ko ghurna aur phir use ye lagna ki hmmlog gaali de rhe hai..phir uska viva me gaand marrnaüòÇüòÇ, cycle pe mera nikhil aur pawan ka triple ride karna, panki ki panauti, amit ka oyo, pawan ki laundiabaazi, ishu ke bina logic ke kuch bhi bol dena pata nhi mazak karke bolta tha ya sach me hi waisa thaüòÇüòÇ...sab bahut yaad aayegaüòçüòç

text:
‚ÄúJha2‚Äù...this is your name in my contact listüòÇ...just to respect youüòú...but you actually deserve it man‚Ä¶‚Äôchapu‚Äô is the most used lingo in iitk ig...people use it on almost everyday, chahe sala wo hag k hi kyo n aaya hoüòÉ...but you are the real ‚Äòchapu‚Äô man...mtlb everywhere‚Ä¶.chahe wo acads ho, chess ho, swimming ho, ya frisbee ho, and yes a poke champion...everywhere man...and itna kuchh krte hue bhi maintaining such a good acads recordüôè...You are such a nice person yar...We didn‚Äôt even talk during our 1st sem, if i‚Äôm correct...again due to hagga partition yar...but i wish ki hmari dosti 1st year se hoti (fir to 1st yr bhi waste kr dete FIFA me üòÉ)...do u remember?The first thing that we talked about was FIFAüòÜ...came to your room...bhai FIFA dal do yar mere dabbe meüòÉ...and waited in your room only, till i got it installed...us din se kya tha, nikal pda mai apne jindgi barbad krne k raho peüòÇ...and that day, i didn‚Äôt expect ki we will eventually become such a good friends...and yes i feel very very lucky that i got one of the nicest human being in my life...you are probably the first maharashtrian, who didn‚Äôt have negative thoughts about biharis,,even at the beginningü§£).  If we talk about the time spent together, kya hi bolu bc, hmesha to kuchh n kuchh krte hi rhta tha tu..always busy...bahut bol diye to sale khel leta tha fifa...but kya hi kr skte tum, dept bhi to gandu hi tha tumharaüòÖ...but still, we did bakchodi...bhar bhar k...played baddi together, and yes your favourite ‚Äòfrisbee‚Äô...initially, i thought ki frisbee is not at interesting at all...but when played, i actually enjoyed it a lot (aur to aur, this sports suits me, less injury possibleüôÇ)...so thank you for making me explore one more sports...you might be good at many things, but bro you need more and more practice in fifa. Do you know why i used to call , particularly you to play fifa??to bring back the confidenceüòÇ...aur wo Rishikesh trip kafi badhiya tha yar...kafi mje kiye hmne...probably the best trip that we could ever make...it was really awesome. 
And, how could i forget that internship prep bro...you really helped me a lot...mtlb that is the time when i started coding, facing a lot of difficulties, but i had not to worry much cause you were there...also, there were a lot of time you helped me for which i will always be grateful to you. So, thank you so much for being the part of my life, and making my college time memorable. And sorry for not coming to Goa, but whenever you make another trip plan, consider me in. aur maine chess khelna start kr diya hai...just for fun...so jb bhi milo, thode tricks btate rhna...All the best for your future...andha paise kmao, aur mera trip sponsor krte rhna...Good luck. Love you bhaiüíñüíì and take care!

text:
Hi Pandey..hope u have moved on by now. I didn‚Äôt want to write anything about you after what you have doneüò†(those who know, know it), but tum dil k kafi achhe aadmi ho‚ù§Ô∏è. Also, I know that it was your last possible chance, so I forgive you. I can write a whole page on this topic..you know that...but i will maintain the dignity of memoir and epsilon amount of  your ijjat. 
We didn‚Äôt talk even once during our 1st year, cause you were maggu at that time...baat krne  k liye kha hi time tha tere pas...and at that time, mere ko ye bilkul ye nhi lga ki we will become such a good friend. From the time I know you, you were the most chillest person of our wing, and ofc Chapu. Do u remember, tumhare pas kafi stories hoti thi , and u needed someone to spill it out. And then you come to most vella guy of the wing, who had always time for others (ofc it was me). That was the time when we got along and the strength of our friendship increased, if u remember. I really enjoyed those stories man (just say thanks from my side to the main storyteller). do u remember, ek din mera laptop aur notebook sb le liye the..just bcz i was not ready to listen to your stories...agle subah quiz thi...b**k aise harkate mt kiya kro, nhi to koi suplex deke chala jayega.I know i hit u once, i‚Äôm really sorry for this...but kya mja aaya tha yar...aisa lga i‚Äôm in wwe ring, and i‚Äôm giving you superman punch. Even after this, we are such a good friend. But i have to ask you a question. Why you always betray me??chahe wo fluid mechanics ki endsem ho ya placement session ho...why??? jaise bhi ho bhai...but tum dil k kafi achhe ho...and it‚Äôs very difficult to find people with a good heart...mai khud ko kafi lucky manta hu ki i got friends like you...playing full night badminton and volleyball...wo bhi kya din the..i really miss those days yar...and yes we haven‚Äôt gone to any trip together, but next time be ready...to sponsor my trip!üòç(JPMC k itne paise ka kya krega). So, thank you for making my life at campus more beautiful and memorable bhai. There is a quote ‚ÄúHope for the best, but be prepared for the worst‚Äù. ‚ÄòWorst‚Äô to tumhare sath ho hi chuka hai, now its time for the best. So, All the best for your future ahead. Bhut paise kamao...Be Rich...Ambani is not that far!
P.S. - You deserve someone better!

author: Mukesh  Kumar

text:
Hello Anshu (pet name revealed)..
Bhai, I just can‚Äôt imagine it‚Äôs been 7 years of friendship..and I wish ki it remains forever‚ù§Ô∏è. It is very difficult for any friendship to go so long. We both are very thankful to god that everything happened in our favour. I came to know you during our JEE preparations at FIITJEE. Initially I thought...ya, seems like a nice guy...started talking...and eventually became good friends while helping each other in solving fiitjee booklets. U remember anshu? that fight between us...MTH publication k book ko leke...i refused to give it to you, and u stopped talking to me...was kidding manüòÇ...and then we became very good friends. This made me realise ki with whoever i had a little nok jhok , they became very good friends of mine (kyo pandey aur piyush üòÇ). We got so lucky bhai‚Ä¶.same batch at FIITJEE, both repeated for JEE, again got in the same institute and batch(Parth Ranker ROCKS(rock emoji)), and fortunately got in the same college and even the same hall bhaiüíó...everything happened in favor of our friendship. And I feel very lucky that you are one of my friends, and trust me, you have a very special place in my lifeü§ó. I mean it needs a lot of effort to maintain any type of relationship, and I respect you a lot for all your efforts to keep our friendship going. 
This whole memoir would be like green trees but with no fruits if I don‚Äôt talk about our college life. You made these whole four years of college life really awesome by showing us your writing skill. Bhai mera SHAYAR..kasam se yar...kya likhte ho bhai..ekdum gaddar...I had only listend earlier ki ‚ÄúPYAR ME LOG SHAYAR BN JATE HAI‚Äù, but you made me believe it. Here is a two-liner that came in my mind spontaneously, hope u like it:
Ek tum aur tera adhoora pyar, i wish ki it happens bar bar;
You might not want it to happen again, but trust me, this will be the reason for your name and fame!
I just can‚Äôt wait to see you on youtube and your book to be a bestseller in India...macha dena bhai! 
And yes, thank you for being there whenever I needed someone. Whenever I was in a confusion for choosing or doing something or not, you were the first person who I went to. And, ofc how can we both forget that traumatic period of my lifeüò¢...man i just can‚Äôt tell how i would have been if u were not there. I am really really thankful to you bhai. And thanks to you for making me start all the nashe thingsüòú...it really feels amazing. Kuchh nashe bache hai, but i know ki tu uski bhi aadat lgwa dega. But, how could I forget that Nainital trip man. Bhai, mai maut ko takk se choo k wapas aa gya tha...it was scary..but i really enjoyed it man. The funniest trip was our regular Patna trip. Sutta fukna at every Patna trip. Jb bhi tum patna aate the, ek lambi list hoti thi tumhare pas, of all the street-food and their locations.Jha bhi jao, ‚Äòpaisa wasool‚Äô ki responsibility tum lete the. Bhai, to ek din bhukha aata tha, paisa wasool krne k liye. and ghar jakar pta chlta tha ki you have gained 5 kgs of weight...i mean are you for real??? And itne khane wale bnde ko achanak se diet follow krna, i can‚Äôt believe my eyes. Jo bhi ho, you are following it strictly, and yes huge respect for this. Aur bhai, wo 85 kg wali bet ko jyada serious mt le yar, gareeb aadmi ko jeene nhi doge kyaüòÇ. The most hilarious and memorable trip to Patna was of course Jan‚Äô21. First of all, you should thank me for making you lose your weights, and saving your auto ka kirayaüòú. We did so much kand bhai...you know that! 
Last but not the least, I wish you very very good luck for your great journey ahead. I hope you fulfill all your dreams, and most importantly follow your diet, cause the ‚ÄòBET‚Äô is still ON.
Love you 3000xüíìüíì
P.S.- tujhe kya, phatna hoga to phat jaunga;
	Apne baap ka khata hu, nikal warna yhi utha k patak dunga!
author: Mukesh  Kumar

author: Piyush

text:
It‚Äôs really hard to express your simplicity and sweetness in words - easily one of the nicest person I know o:)Have seen you inside out (You know what I mean :P)..shouldn‚Äôt go into details on public records. Some things about you really intrigue me - how can someone play all day long (you should be the poster boy of Glucon-D) and have so much organised hostel room (Dude, really WTF!, they are not supposed to be organised in the first place :-)). 
It was a pleasure being your script-writer from Nishika in fresher to Minki in senior year...chutiya tmhara kata...but dukh hmko bhi hua ;)...I guess they didn‚Äôt know you have 6-pack abs, a good job and a kind soul (Khud so jaayenge usko‚Ä¶..)..oh that qualifies you for marriage (already late by Rajasthani standards xD).. can wait to share your rangeen hostel kisse with bhabhi-sa (it‚Äôs time to forget Kristen Stewart).
Your room has always been our backchodi adda...your Gurgaon flat will be one too :) You are better than a bank when it comes to safeguarding money but you used to steal my roomie and his shipment..very bad! ;) Just a friendly reminder - I play better badminton and mini-militia than you. Period. Most probably you would agree, if not, I do have ice cream.
I have got your back just like that Antaragni night dare. Have roamed around a lot together, still, a lot left to explore.  It would be near impossible for someone to know you and not like you for the person you are. Thanks for always being there except PHY103 endsem...hahaha!!. Love you, bro! M just a call away! All the best! A very bright future awaits!
P.S - Is sem to firse dassa aarha hoga !?

text:
You were a hard nut, thankfully I had Meena to help me crack you up. You are a bit moody and sometimes seriously mess up. Hopefully, you remember a few quarrels we had but it turned out fine in the end. Having DOPA as roommate has its own perk and I must say, you have a very well-curated collection :P got a lot of exposure from you -from CCD‚Äôs devils own to good English music, from GOT to the vixen, and many more.

Your attention to minute and keen sense of design is remarkable. Most people here do things that will either fetch good grades or land them a fat job. In that sense, you were very different. Though sometimes overdone, I like your ‚ÄòDoing only things I like‚Äô attitude i.e I remember you watching ‚ÄòThe Office‚Äô instead of studying for Endsem but at the same time putting extra hours to learn Sanskrit and philosophy! 

Do u remember our intense philosophical discussions especially in CCD and those late-night walks afterwards (Wo Jaan Jaan kehke jaan le gye) ?..good old days!  Intelligent to ho hi sir aap bs put your ass to work! All the best! Happy researching! 
B-319 ka tempo high hai!

Gadhi pe hasna, tera oyozone hona, TA ki gand maarna, meri tatti kismat pe rona, paper se pehle sath me hagna, tere bhand hone ke baad baate sunna, Hall 7 toh nahi bhulunga bhai, First year me Pandey ko pareshan karna, OAT ‚ù§Ô∏è, mujhe ulti karake sulane ke liye thanks, mera rr roz sunna, kattar hindu banna (Jai Shree Ram), Pankaj ke maze lena, din bhar tere room me pade rehna, bhai summer kaise bhul gaya tu, kaise pada rehta tha mai tere room me ü§£, roz 12 baje tujhe canteen bulana, Rishab tu aur mai bakchodi karna, tere aur Rishab ke jhagde aur usme mai aag lagata tha ü§£, gandu ek aur bhul gaya tu - Phy103 ke paper ke ek raat pehle library me bakchodi karna, 8-10 bhaiyo pe hasna, MOS dono baar (A ya B toh lag hi jaega madarchod ü§£), class bunk karke ccd canteen jana, Das ki dukaan, tujhe pehli baar daaru pilana, tera bihari naam karan karna, aauga bolna, subah YJHD dekhna aur gaane me background dancer pe hasna...
Aur kitna kuch hai bsdk..
Aakhri ek saal toh isse jyada bakchodi karni hai, ab paisa bhi hoga üòå, pure 4 saal ki khunnas ek me nikal lenge.. Khulega campus bhai.. Bakchodiya baaki hai... College life meri itni bakchod huyi hai aur safal huyi hai toh uska main reason Tu aur Rishab ho.. Love you brother.

PS- Mujhe ab bhi yaad hai pehli baar kaise mile the.. Paki ke room pe tu nanga khada tha aur tab sirf apan dono the jinko Dani pasand thi.. Dani is lub ‚ù§Ô∏è
Tab ye expect nahi kiya tha apan aise dost banege..
(Unexpected friendships are the best ones)
Jaldi mil bsdk. Saal ke upar ho gaya!

Too bad I only got to talk to you a bit during the final year of campus :"). But I did have a nice time being an ESC101 Tutor with you and you have always been a friendly and approachable guy to talk to. All the best for your future ahead man! Hope we remain in touch :)
author: Prateek  Varshney

text: Hey Ayush! Funnily I only got to know about you first during second year's ICPC (Which we didn't even prepare for, gave it on a whim XD and just missed narrowly :")). Usse pehle I didn't know ki yeh banda kon hai. And us din ke baad you did not let me forget at all :). Acads, Coding, Consulting, Finance pata nhi kya kya tumne ek saath sambhala hai. And ab JPMC bhi! Always been a big admirer of the hard work you have put it to achieve all this man. All the best for your life ahead bhai! And don't forget us muggles :)
author: Prateek  Varshney

text:
Hey Deepak. Roz tera yearbook page kholke baith jaata hu kyuki samajh hi nhi aata kab aur kaha se shuru karu mai. Socha aaj pehla attempt maar hi lu. Toh first draft samajh ke baksh dena :P.

Thanks for being at the receiving end of rants, cribs and everyday rr. Tune naa sirf har baar sunaa (voh bhi itni dheeraj ke saath), par apna valuable feedback diya and har bar mujhe calm down kiya. And most importantly, you were always there as a rock for me to fall and rely on. Tere bina toh mai DE courses katai clear nhi kar paata. Raat bhar padna aur phir exam se pehle mujhe padana aur mere doubts clear karna. You even took the blame for me for some of my fuckups in courses! I can't express how grateful I am to have you as a friend during my stay here.

You're the guy who made me fall into love with memes, wholesomeness, shayari, gazal, music and literature. Bhai maine tujhe kitni baar kaha hai, apni kavitao ko publish kar par tu sunta hi nhi -_-. Pata nhi kyu khud ki talent ki kadr hi nhi karta. Thank you for the daily dose of dopamine and serotonin via the memes and music you send my way on a daily basis. Sometimes that is all one needs to drag through their mundane day and life :). 

Keep on spreading happiness man. And ab jaate jaate apne time management ke raaz bhi batate jaa :P. Counselling, HSS, acads, memes aur pata nhi kya kay ek saath sambhal leta hai XO. Thanks for being such an integral part of my campus life.  Bas jald se noida aa phir chill karte apan saath mein :P. Wishing you all the best for your life ahead. And once again, Thank you! ^_^
author: Prateek  Varshney

text: Hey man! You're one of the most approachable people I have come to interact with during my stay here. Talking to you would always help calm my nerves. And I'll leave the emphasizing your "chaapuness", your extraordinary ability to handle acads and code so freaking well to others. All the best for your life ahead, man! And don't forget us muggles :)

text: Yo Dindor, mujhe achhe se yaad hai apna pehla interaction Ostwal ke through hua thaa jab apan log assignment karne ke liye adda dhund rahe thei aur staff canteen mein jaakar baith gaye. Can't forget the SOC171 prep during first year bhai. Pata nhi kaise tum log aise hi kitaab "samajh" ke chale jaate thei exam dene. Mujhse toh kabhi yeh nhi ho paaya. Mujhe toh ratna hi pad jaata thaa har baar :"). And PSY499 mein toh agar tum nhi hote toh shayad hi meri naiyya paar ho paati. Sahi mein. Aur bhai tumhari acting acting skills and dramatics ki taraf shiddat ki jitni tareef karu utni kam hai. Shayad hi mujhe koi aur campus mein mil paaya hoga poore 4 saal mein jo tum jaise kaghaz pe sirf likhta nhi thaa par bhavnaao ko shaboo se jodkar bayaan karta thaa. Aakhri kuch dino mein tumhari shayari pe shayari sunkar toh mazaa hi aagaya thaa mujhe. And haa, tanks thanks for introducing me to ecstasy :P. Kaafi mazaa aaya kyuki teri company jo saath mein thi. Bas ab jald hi UPSC ke bahane hi sahi Delhi aa phirse milke "chill" karna hai tere saath :). All the very best for your life bhai! Aur touch mein rehna. Jald hi milte hai! :)
author: Prateek  Varshney

text: Yo Sid Jay! You're one of the sweetest persons I have come to know during my campus stay. But your time management and organisation skills is something I've always admired. Thanks for helping me out during the Pre-Doc interviews. All the best for your life ahead, both personal and professional (not that you need any :P)! And don't forget us muggles :)
author: Prateek  Varshney

text:
Hey Vishesh! Apni wing mein acads ko lekar sabse mehnati insaan tum hi ho. I was literally jaw dropping when i saw you being able to recall almost every MTH101 solution from memory. And then seeing you run after the prof and the AMs just because you were not able to solve one question in the entire assignment sheets. Tumhari mehnat aur shiddat ki jitni tareef karu utni kam hai. And end mein mehnat rang le hi aayi. You were finally able to drop the MECH moniker and now look at you. Adobe mein intern kar rahe and ab toh PPO bhi mil jayega tumhe :)

I am also inspired by your competitive drive bhai. Especially in sports. I have seen you go all out in basketball and badminton to snatch that one basket or that one point against the opponent (which also makes me shit scared at times of being on the same team as you :P). Ab toh Ronaldo aur Dhoni se dushmani chhod do. Kitni baar OAT khush hokar gaye ho aur dukhi hokar vapas aaye ho (:. *coughs* Portugal vs Spain *coughs* CSK vs DC *coughs* :P. Bas thoda competitive drive mein aakar thoda hosh ka bhi dhyaan rakha karo. Not gonna say more since mujhe footpath pe safely chalne ki opportunity nhi chhodni hai. Hehe.

Aur jab tum khud masti ke mood mein hote ho tab toh mazaa hi aajata hai. Thanks for providing (i.e., being) the template for so many memes and stickers (:. All the best for your future ahead bhai, both personal and professional. And stay in touch. Jaldi Delhi shift ho jaa chill karenge apan. Cheers! :)

Hye Kanishka.......
1st time i met you was on result day of 2019 election.. innocent, introvert type girl...then phir summer me wo bithoor trip jaha se hamlog sayad hamari dost ki start hue the...... and whole summer hamri dosti kaffi acchi ho gaye...... you were always so unique in my life.. the way you was and the way you took care of me... i still remember those dinners in hall 10.. walking late night and having ice creams and sometimes exploring the unseen part of academic area. I don't know what was that in between us during that time but when you used to share all your stuffs with me.. it always felt me special.... and one of the region i started liking you during that time. kahir it soon ended and the whole covid time took things away from me. 
with all this the way you  said good bye was unique too i never expected we will have a end like this. per theek hai hamesha ke trah kya hi farq padta hai... thankyou for everything. and this time i won't say sorry... pata nai maine koi galti ki bhi hai ya nai.. per agar kuch ki hai to  ho sake to bata dena.....bye...dhyan rakh.....
and i don't want this to be approved.......

author: Rajan  Singh

text:
Yo Sachin Boiii

Yaar campus mai final goodbye bolne ka mauka bhi nahi mila. Ye memoir uski jagah to nahi le sakta par koshish hi sahi. Waise to poori athletics family hi mast thi apni, but I really loved to spend time with you, walking and discussing. Just standing by your side I felt happy. But, playing by your side was altogether a different ball game. Chahe koi bhi volleyball ka match ho, chahe samne koi bhi kyo na ho. Playing with you on the net was an experience in itself. Watching you take those smashes was an absolute delight and so was bitching the other team. 

Itni sari memories to hai hi apni summer camp ki, Blueworld ki, Ganga-barrage ki, Inter IIT ki and Udghosh ki, sportech ki, and itni dher sari treats. But I really loved the one in which you came to take me to OAT for my birthday celebration. Or us IME wale course mai A lag gaya üòÇ pata nahi kaise. Or bhi na jane kitna kuch hai, par tumhe to sab pata hi hai.
  
May you do wonders and marvels in whichever field you chose to pursue. 
Would love to sit together one day and discuss all about our adventures and journey so far.
author: Rajan  Singh

text:
Aur bhai Jumper...

Kaisa ho. Bhai bilkul sahi kaha tune athlete to tu hai hi accha sath hi sath banda bhi tu ekdam mast hai. Par mera first impression tera aisa nahi tha. First year mai mujhe hamesha se lagta tha ki ekdam jat budhi insan hai tu. Tab lagta tha ki koi kuch bologe isse to ab ye bolega - 
"Re samajh mai na ari thare baat, tabhi kahi se scorpio ayegi and rehpat lagage ke baith ke usme chala jayega üòÇüòÇüòÇüòÇ"

Yeah, I know I have a bad habit of forming terrible first impressions of people. Par kisi insan ke bare mai shayad isse jyada galat nahi ho sakta tha. Yaar kitna funloving and cheerful banda hai tu. Tune kabh bhi jumpers par kare gaye jokes ko dil par nahi liya. Kabhi bhi phone karke ke scorpio wagera nahi bulayi kabhiüòÇüòÇ. 

Par sahi mai yaar respect to hai yaar tere liye as a sportsperson. From ground mai pole se gadde karne üòÖse competetions mai jhande gadne tak. you really have put in lot of effort and come so far. 

Will really miss going on countless treats with you guys and maknig jokes on jumpers (just kidding ). Playing volleyball with you guys, having countless of bulla sessions at the mess table. 
All the best for your future and aise hi nayi nayi uchaiyoo ko chute rehna.

text:
Yo ChooseBeta!!! üòÉ
Yaad hai tujhe, first year ke end mein donon ke bhaiyon ne dhokha diya tha agle saal room share karne se. Aur phir uske baad hm donon mile the üòÖ. Dukh mein ek dusre ke saathi!!! Phir uske baad first year summer, 2nd year, 3rd year, bas tu hin tha mujhe jhelne wala ek. üòÇ
Tmlog kitna MM khelte the, aur mujhe uske controls tatti lagte the. Although hmlogon ne badminton, PUBG, cards, Monopoly, aur pata nahin kya kya saath mein khela hai. 
2018 summer mein donon saath mein kaam kiye the on that full-stack development project. Kitni mehnat se tune apna naam dalwaya tha... Aur last day pe BBQ mein party ki thi hmlogon ne üòé.
Then tera fitness enthu, jo 2nd year mein jaaga. Aur tune 5K bhi bhaag liya! 
PUBG mein toh phod dete the sab, jab bhi khelte the saath mein üòé. 
Tu toh apna yoga guru ban gaya tha üòÖüòÖüòÖ. Aise karo, yeh karo, isse yeh hoga, usse woh hoga, ... üôáüèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è. Aur saath mein diet planner. Tera woh white board par likha hua "kachcha chaba ja" ab bhi wahin likha hai ü§£. 
Tere saath wali Lucknow trip was very memorable. Although non-veg khane ke liye tune mujhe akela chhor diya tha üòï. Aur han, uss shaam ko kaise bhul sakte hain. You went into a mall, changed from jeans to shorts. And then returned back to kanpur in those shorts only ü§£. Telling that these are more comfortable...
Phir teri knee problem and then we saw a completely different Ashish in front of us. Your dedication to come out of it was marvelous. Ab toh tu fitness freak ban gaya hai üòÖ, spending most of your time in gym. Waise ghar mein hin gym kholne ka mera idea tha mast üòé. Ab hme bhi free ka gym gyaan dete rehna üòú.
Waise ek afsos zaroor hoga. Tmse last month mil nahin paane ka... But still, aage milenge toh zaroor mere dost üôåüèª. Phir party karenge...

All the best for the future bro. Aise hin MACHATE raho. Aur hme bhul mat jana üòÖ.

text: The idiosyncrasies of mine were put to use on you the very first week we quite fortuitously met, and thanks to your innocence they did but exacerbate the situation. To a great extent it produced the sensation of mirth, and my fastidiousness towards being didactic "by scandalizing" of course. It was in the months that followed that I discovered your diffidence, and your helpful nature rendered our initial exchanges ephemeral. It did span out to involving discussions at the Hall 5 Canteen over my upcoming B grades or the ‡¶Æ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ï‡¶æ situation, when your confession "of not being able to sleep one whole night" proved totally iconoclastic to the presumption of your nerdiness. Well, things did flow smoothly since then, with Microcap discussions or lab report exchanges, and it was very slow and natural for me to value the bond we developed as a capricious one. Believe you me, you were someone I always knew I could bank on, and so I did hours before EC lab exam, and still Mazhari f**ked me over with wave-shaping. Occasional discussions of astrophysics and dark matter, more lab report exchanges, my B grades and how I'd rue the day I joined IITK, and a caring friendly ear provided by you, did make up for one hell of a ride! Hope we meet soon!!
author: Sagnik  Bhattacharya

text: It's a shame to have to write a memoir to express the plethora of stuff we have gone through together, but here goes. It all started out with this "A4 sheet for TA101" discussion, you were an introvert cute guy back then. Then it went on to become those red sauce pasta breaks during the first semester exams and we bonded over food and gossiping about some people behind their backs, which might have been the main focus of my time at IITK. Then you abruptly became the FIFA boy and our pasta breaks were cute short by Pulkit forcefully (as always) entering your life with his (poor) FIFA skills. We discussed courses and Pulkit, and I always had the vibe of a good human being coming from you, but you did something by saving me from that third semester incident that I had never expected. I started respecting you as a person with high integrity, and that as it comes by, is rare. Then you became the face of E-Cell, and did a fantastic job at it, which more than one achievement coming your way (double meaning intended). I miss our EE340 tutorials, were we always took the last row and discussed useless topics of gossip. I wish we could spend more time, but I do believe I have gotten to know you a lot; would like to keep in touch, and hope to meet you soon. All the best for your future!!

text: I borrowed this one from work, and, afraid of doing damage to its white binding, I bought a cloth cover, originally no doubt intended for bibles, to protect the book from smudges or anything else untoward. That covering became symbolic as I dived into this memoir of hiding, transformation, and reversals. In the Darkroom follows feminist scholar Susan Faludi as she reunites with her estranged father, who is now living as a woman in the Budapest of her youth. Her father survived the Holocaust through disguises and subterfuge, then found refuge after the war in depictions of women on film; she is proud to show her daughter the life she has made in Budapest, even as right wing nationalism grows around her. Susan Faludi frankly discusses her struggle to accept her father, both in her estrangement and in her new life as woman, and reading the memoir of an old school feminist figure out how to be trans-inclusive is one of the most heartwarming things you‚Äôll ever come across.

text:
Tera itna bada name hai aur kaam bhi bade bade hi krta hai, 
Tere se first din mila aur sath me orientation k sessions aur tab se hamara bonding kya mast raha. Sath me kaam krna hamesha mazzedar rha phir chahe wo summer project(first project at IITK) ho ya aeromodelling ka workshop. SOC me tumne kya kaam kiya, wrna on time project nahi ho pata. Yaad hai SOC k demo day se pahle kis tarah last k web pages banaye the hamne. 
ECO101 k tips and guidance wala incident yaad rahega and uske baad k bhi bahot courses/projects k.
Bhai tum always crisis time pr sath rahe ho phir wo koi bhi academic decision lena ho ya career planning ho. Tu chaapu aur cool hai ye first year me hi pta chal gya tha jab tu chemical se mech me branch change krna chahta tha (still ye EPIC tha mere liye aur sun kr hassi aa jati hai)
Sath me kafi memories hai birthday parties, Liquid treat, mess aur canteen k discussions, specially wo geetam k room pr pizza party and bulla session. 
Mujhe tere pr gussa tab aaya tha jab tumne shift kr liya 6 top me third year me aur late se btaya and tab kuch nahi kr skta tha mai :(

text: Eklaute aise mitra mere college ke jise kisi aur se zyada dosti krte dekhkr jalan hone lagti thi mujhe. Sabka kaam apne sir pr lene ko duty maanane wala aur har cheez ki councelling krne wala. Pata nhi mai kaise tumhe sahi lag gya pr thanks roomie banane ke liye. Summers me project krna, jiske sapne me pubg aa jaata tha, seeti bajana aur seekhna, swimming, bady, football, basketball, cricket aur har ek gaane ka lyrics yaad rakhna, snt me jeetna chahe apna project ho ya fir inter iit me doosron ka project ho. Yahan tk elections me jitwana. Kya kya nhi kiya tumne?? Mai batata hoon waise ki catch haanth failaa kr bhaagte hue krne ka try kya mast tha.   . Haan tum jab bhi party me bulaane ke liye yeh kehte the ki tum nhi jaaoge toh mai bhi nhi jaaunga uspr mana kr paana bohot mushkil ho jaata tha pr vo kaafi achha lagta tha mujhe, thanks. Are yaar tareef krne me ajeeb lag raha hai, aage firse nhi krunga  kabhi Miss Soumyaaa. Pata nhi chala ek toh ladki ka naam hai ya ladke ka. author: Shivam Kumar (B Kumar)

text:
Eklaute aise mitra mere college ke jise kisi aur se zyada dosti krte dekhkr jalan hone lagti thi mujhe. Sabse zyada innocent aur starting me toh bilkul bhi oppose nhi krne wala but isiliye taaki saamne wale ko bura na lage. Sabka kaam apne sir pr lene ko duty maanane wala aur har cheez ki councelling krne wala. Pata nhi mai kaise tumhe sahi lag gya pr thanks roomie banane ke liye. Summers me project krna, jiske sapne me pubg aa jaata tha, seeti bajana aur seekhna, swimming, bady, football, basketball, cricket aur har ek gaane ka lyrics yaad rakhna, snt me jeetna chahe apna project ho ya fir inter iit me doosron ka project ho. Yahan tk elections me jitwana. Kya kya nhi kiya tumne?? Mai batata hoon waise ki catch haanth failaa kr bhaagte hue krne ka try kya mast tha. . Haan tum jab bhi party me bulaane ke liye yeh kehte the ki tum nhi jaaoge toh mai bhi nhi jaaunga uspr mana kr paana bohot mushkil ho jaata tha pr vo kaafi achha lagta tha mujhe, thanks. Are yaar tareef krne me ajeeb lag raha hai, aage firse nhi krunga kabhi Miss Soumyaaa. Pata nhi chala ek toh ladki ka naam hai ya ladke ka. Saath me har kaam krne ke liye bohot achha companion choose kiya tha tumne. Welcome welcome. Haan last day likh raha hoon pr sabse pehle tumhara hin likh raha hoon. All the best jo kr rhe ho uske liye. Ab maine wish kr diya toh pakka ho hin jaana hai. Welcome welcome. Thanks padha dene ke liye aur naiyaa paar lagwaa dene ke liye. Youtube pr gaana loop me laga kr jab tum gaana gaate the tbhi maine tumhe apne band ke liye as a singer recruit kr liya tha. Jldi thoda ab time mile bus aur wapas se maze kr paayein jo krte the. Aapas me humesha ek doosre ko chidhana bus baakiyon ke saamne milkr unko chidhane me kaafi maza aata tha. Thanks for being my bestestest Male (vo samjh rhe ho naa) friend. 
Uncle ko vo wale messages ka kahani batane wale aur na jaane kitno ke dil todne wala ladka. Saathe me dhoni ko jitwaane ka kitna try nhi kiya humne. Humare hin superstitions ke wajah se hin waise jeeta hai vo. ‚ÄúBut they never did, ever lived, ebbing and flowing Inhibited, limited‚Äù se lekr ‚Äúare you ready?? Dhu dhu dhu dhu dhu.. Surwaan bhi 16va vi tappeya 17va vi tappeya (what!) 18ve ‚Äòch munda badnam ho gaya‚Äù gaana gaane tak ka safar kaafi achha raha. 
Yaar us mote animeda ne jo anime hunter x hunter dikhaya tha toh kya new year manaye the hum log. Shrotriya ek shift krta tha aur fir hum dono doosre shift me. Aur yaar thanks jo daant daant kr aur taana maar maar kr mujhe class le jaate the. Ek time hota tha jab sab humare room me ikattha hote the fir vo kuch hua pata nhi shayad bed alag alag kr diye the galti se shayad. Tbhi se pata nhi kyun kam krte gye. Yaar aur darwaaza band krke padhne time ek toh aawaz bhi nhi aa paati thi knock ki. Chill hai vo toh. 
Achhe achhe idea dene ke liye thanks ki kaise chupaaun aur kya krun my better half se baat krne ke liye. Pata nhi papa mummy ko itne bhole kyun lagte ho tum ki dekho Shivam ek soumya bhi hai aur ek tum ho. Unhe kya pata ki yhi hai jise sab pata hai. 
Waise summers me mai maan chuka tha ki tum roomie toh noi hin banoge toh mai poochna hin nhi chah raha tha. Lagta tha karan aur tum hin banoge. Pr fir ban gye hum dono roomie mast tumne pooch liya tha.  
Vo raat ke 4 bje tk badi khelne me bhi kaafi maza aata tha yaar. Fir beech me jab Counter strike ka chaska laga tha. Kaafi kam time ke liye pr maza kaafi aaya tha. Salman khan ke maha bhakt ho tum. Uske jaisa bracelet pehenne tk toh theek tha. Pr tumne toh uske birthday ke din hin apna rakh liya. Aisa kyun?? 
Are waise mujhe kya topi pehnaya tha tumne standup time mere jokes ki tareef kr krke, jab mai room me practice kr raha tha. Fir wapas jab apne us video ko dekhta hoon tb lagta hai kya hin dooston ke kehne pr aakr kiya. 
Waise us din jab basket ball ground pr hum log baat kr rhe the, toh kaash jo un pujari uncle ne bataya hoga tumhe, vo galat nikla ho. Are waise itne mehnat se padha tha tumne pschyology pr afsos wapas se tumhare lottery me vhi mila tumko(ek lauta course jo hum wingies se zyada tumhara saath nhi choodna chahta tha). Darawne movie ka crazy, jaise a quite place dhekte time mai sahi me darr kr chilla deta tha toh yeh daant deta tha ki mai jaanboojh ke kr raha hoon. Thanks tumne lone ranger dekh liya ultimately. Nhi toh use dekhte time 500 baar toh soo chuke ho tum. Lights off krke mahaul jama kr movie laga kr khud soo jata tha.
HAr cheez hum dono kaafi enthu se start krte the phir lastly tum mera bojh bhi utha kr khud complete krte the. Hackathons dena microsoft, flipkart ka ya fir raat bhar rust ka, ya fir reinforcement learning ke liye vo car khareedne ke planning krna. Robots aur insaan pr discuss krna aur poore time bulla kaatna saath me. 
Tumhari galat sangat ke wajah se hin maine BBQ me mocktail piya tha aur uske baad room pr aakr (aage continue krna hai kya)?? Apni first conversation hui thi bhoot ki baaton se pr tumhare aawaz joki tum ishq mubaarak gaa rhe the usne mera dhayan aakarshit kiya tha. Jldi se corona khatam ho aur milein toh isi gaane pr ab casio bajayenge (Zara zara toh bhoto baja liye kyun). Chalo padhne jaao ab, kaafi time chala gya tumhara. Waise thanks again, college ke almost har achhe memories me tum rhe ho. is baar bus college aa jaate toh shayad mai utna bore nhi hota. Maze kaafi kiye but jo maze krne ka average level set ho chuka tha tumhare saath usse kam hin reh paaya.

text:
Remember the first time we met? 
I was contesting for Senator and I didn't know any girl to get us into GH for campaigning. Luckily, Saransh had a girlfriend. Thanks for agreeing to let us into GH. I remember mere campaigners kitne excited the first time GH me jaane je liye and Atul kitna gussa hua tha jab use pata chala ki ID card ke bina GH me nahi jaa sakte.

Tumhari lab reports ke liye thanks yaar! Khudse lab report likhne ka motivation kahan se aata tha tumhare andar?

GI lab to altogether ek alag hi experience tha! Itni exhausting lab me bhi tum log ki wajah se itna interesting time beeta; itni saari baatein and snacks from CC canteen. 

The long conversations on the video calls were such a great memory!

Whenever you read this... let's get together for another video call

author: Siddharth  Jayashankar

text:
I am sure everyone knows how hardworking you are, how intelligent you are and yada yada yada (who the f**k doesn't ever get even close to getting a B what the f**k man!).

I still remember the first memory I have of you was the first year when the Prof was trying to derive some detailed result, and midway in his second page he gets stuck. After few minutes of utter silence and confusion, I one guy (out of the odd 400) pointing out that he did a small error somewhere in the first page (!!) of the proof. The image I had of you then is the same I have of you know. Super focused and Super confident.

I think we got to know each other better from the third-semester thermodynamics and in the time we spent together, I have come to know that you are one of the most helpful and honest guys I have ever met (and probably will meet). Sounds cliche? But people often underestimate the importance of being honest to yourself and others in terms of having a long-term friendship. That is something I will take with me forever.

This memoir can't encapsulate how grateful I am for getting me through this undergrad (special mention to that horrible "apping" season of 2019-2020). I would never really understand why you chose to be friends with me, help and guide me in almost all walks of life, and share my love for food and music. 

Although we didn't get the chance to invade our beloved base in the 8th semester (I was anyways planning not to be around in my 7th), you have always been a text away, ready to help/offer your honest criticism. I hope we stay that way forever. Now I know, this won't change anything but please please please please please decide against the K-word we are not allowed to speak about.

Cheers to good times, that were and that will be.
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
Hey Sidjay, you were the very first guy I talked to outside of my wing, and at that time, I was completely unaware of how strong of a friendship we were going to develop.

I used to frequent libraries in my first year, and that was when I got to know that you are studious. I think I have debated once in my whole life in first year Galaxy and you broke me down to shreds (Well I really enjoyed that experience nonetheless). After that, in the 3rd semester, we used to discuss discrete math and other CS courses in the library. I still remember how we both were struggling in discrete, and in the end, you took some hiatus and then emerged victorious after that endsem (LoL). 

There are a bunch of people that are hardworking in IITK and a bunch of intelligent people. But believe me when I say this, that I have seen no other person that is as sharp and intelligent and at the same time as dedicated and hardworking as you. The reason that you do so well in debates is the same reason that you do so well in courses. You are genuinely curious to understand anything and everything thrown at you and give it your all until you know. Our beloved 4th semester and your beloved Thermo course will always be a cherished memory. You choosing to make fun of a professor and then securing an A* from the same guy, is a story I would love to recite many more times.  Apart from that in almost every course (atleast till the time you were in IITK), be it you teaching me 220 and OS,  be it TA Lab (Oh god the things I had to hear!) or Machine Learning (the low effort A*), we have shared some great memories. During the internship season, I got to know that you are not like the rest of us who would do something they are not interested in, just because everyone else is doing it or not. It was inspiring for me and played a significant role in giving me the confidence to give up on the conventional route and work on what I truly want to. Thanks for that.

My heart swells with happiness whenever you do something extraordinary (which is very often, of course) because I want people like you to climb the food chain. I am more sure than anyone else that you will achieve whatever you want to and lots more. Will try my best to keep in touch and meet whenever possible.

Cheers SidJay!

text:
Yo Abhyuday!

You have inspired me a lot throughout the campus journey. I have seen the true meaning of "Aim so high that other people's goals are the basic minimum of your goals". I don't think IITK has seen many people with more A*s than A. And the best part is you make it seem so effortless. 

Most people know you just by your acads but from what conversations we have had, I see you as a person with much more depth. You understand things, you know what you have to do and unlike many others, you actually do what you know you have to do! That's why I respect your work ethic and get inspired by it.

Let's make things happen! See you soon. 

PS: I will definitely be rooting for you as our PM. üòâ

text:
Yo Shringi!

These 4 years were super fun around you. Lol, I have lost the count of assignments we have done together. And more than that the hours of debugging we have put in. I still got all our "debugging successful" pics! I never had to worry about any concept which I didn't understand in RM101 because I always had Room 316 as the backup. Really dude, acads were so stress-free because I had you around. Thanks a lot for that. üòÑ

I have seen you grow a lot in terms of dealing with people in the last 4 years. Good job! üòÅ

I really loved the times when we 3 used to go to the mess together, mock each other a bit, laugh a lot, then come back and play 3C2 chess matches! It was a home-like feeling, that 1/4th of the wing which we had for ourselves! Those days were super fun.

More than anything else, I have always loved our level of understanding about each other's thought process be it in a theoretical concept or a code or a life situation. We understand each other very well. That's why it's so easy to talk to you and explain to you and understand from you regarding literally everything. 

And lastly, in these 4 years, it's so easy to lose yourself and do things which you wouldn't have wanted to do just because everyone else around you is doing it. In that sea of people, I have always found you and Shobhit as my reference points, or more of an existential proof in not doing certain things which I didn't want to. Thanks for that grounding! 

And yes, I will soon clear my Marvel Backlog :p

text:
Hi Prateek! Honestly given 57 memoirs about you have been written I'm pretty sure ab I'll also end up saying all the same things over. I'll start off with the first year, your double 10. I personally didn't like the fact that you and Priyanshu were always by the books and would hardly put a foot wrong when it came to managing your time. That image of you walking by the stairs at 3 AM with the Sociology book in hand is a pretty powerful one and perfectly captures what turned out to be the right decision which paid off with the eventual outcome. 

In the second and third year, I would go on to see you sleeping in all sorts of positions, at completely random times in anyone's bed but your own. You were also probably one of the first person who brought the group together for Poker/ Mafia though you wouldn't end up playing as much as everyone else didüòíüòí. Out of all the people whom I wanted to extract information and gossip from, you were most definitely the toughest. Your "Tum kuch bhi puch lo, mai bata dunga", was obviously a big fat lie üòêüòê. 

Ab jab bhi Google karunga tumhari shakal yaad ayegi üò§üò§. Thanks for being such an overachiever, but Neurbiology mein mere hi zyada the üòéüòé. text:
Suspecy bhai kya kya leekhu..
Itna kuch to hai leekhne ko..

Ek to mene tere ko naam hi diya hai "suspecy" uske liye thanks bolna mujhe..

And mujhe to vo time yaad aa raha jab tu..
Hamko samjhata tha ki "Fail to koi hota hi nahi hai" first sem me..
Alag hi maze aate the baate sun ne me..
Ussi karan ESC101 ki lab beech me chod ke canteen jaa rahe the...Antaragni me jaa rahe rahe the..Maze kar rahe the full..

Uske baad 2nd sem me..LIF101 ki class me saath jaana..Attendance ke marks k liye üòÇüòÇ


ESC201 to kabhi nahi bhul sakta me..
Naa tu bhul sakta...
Midsem me ek question bana usme bhi resistance negative me aa gaya...

Lab exam se phele pta nahi breadboard kya hota haiüòÇüòÇüòÇ...
Tune bhai pori raat padha diya..Course nikalwa diya. .

Or ESC201 ka endsem naa to tu bhul sakta naa me.. or naa hi MriganküòÇ..

Alag level scene chal rahe the..

SOC479 me "Oh pen le jaana to bhul hi gaya"üòÇüòÇ

Fir uske baad lockdown me tere ko phone par pakaana..
Placement naa hone par tere se batana...

Tune bs ek line boli vo kaam kar gayi " chinta naa kar kuch naa kuch acha kar hi lega..Last me kuch acha ho hi jaayega"..

Bhai last ke din to alag yaad rahenge..
SIS gaurd ke saath ka time üòÇ...

Mst the last k din..Lyrics samjhana .. Punjabi gaane samjhana..

Bs last uske baad nahi lunga abüòÇüòÇsmjh raha hai na..


Bhai sahi the 4 saal maze aaye...


Aage milte hai kabhi pakka utne hi maze karenge
author: Yogeshwar

text:
Bhai..
1st sem me rohit pandey waala prank me maza aaya, fir tere maze liye itne. ..Chintu ke room me..Fir ladaai bhi hui..

Saini ne jab "delete for me" waala kaam kiya tab bhi hassi aayi bhot...

Ab apna dhyan rakhna ..Or jaldi hi milte hai kabhi..
author: Yogeshwar

text:
I saw you first time on 22nd July 2017, obviously the first day of IITK. We were in the same cab, And your unique voice can be recognized even in the crowded auditorium of 830 students.
Shuruaat me to koi baat hi nahi hui.. and 3rd year me saath me project mila, you have a dominating nature at that time, jesse tum baat baat par bolti thi ki "Tumse bola tha karne ko to kyu nahi kiya" and kaafi daata tumne uss project me mujhe. 
uske ek saal baad firse project partner ban gaye..üòÇüòÇ coincidentally... iss baar mujhe lag raha tha ki daant to nahi khaani tumhari.. to saara kaam kar diya time se..
CHE352 ke baad socha nahi tha kabhi itne ache dost ban paayenge..

"Maybe you have to know the darkness before you can appreciate the light." and you are much "brighter" and way more mature than I think earlier.

""‡§Ø‡§π ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§Ø ‡§ï‡§¨ ‡§¨‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§™‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§®‡§æ ‡§ö‡§≤‡§æ‡•§
‡§™‡•Ä‡§õ‡•á ‡§ï‡§ø‡§§‡§®‡•Ä ‡§Ø‡§æ‡§¶‡•á ‡§¨‡•Å‡§® ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§™‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§®‡§æ ‡§ö‡§≤‡§æ !!""

Suggestions: Always keep one platform open for communication üòÇüòÇ
don't think too much ... tum bhot zyada sochti ho choti choti cheezo ke baare me... then pareshaan hoti ho.. 
life ko jiyo jitna jee sakti ho...
I know pichle 4 saal kitni mehnat ki hai tumne..

And always remember one thing, at the end of the day, everything will be alright. 
"last me sab acha hi hoga"

Gravity se leke teri gaand tak kya kuch nahi dekha hai 4 saal me xD Bohot saaari memories hain apni toh. Grateful for all your advice and inputs on everything over the years. Chemical se Batti se CSE se Maths ki teri journey kaafi tough par achi rahi hai maine dekha hai. Bhai source bethao ghar pe scene banane ka yaar mera bhi apna toh tumne badiya set karliya hai. author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
Gandhi sir fluids nikalwane ke liye thanks! Tere bina A toh nahi hi lagta end sem tak mai itna pareshan ho gaya tha uss course se. Also wo prof ka monotonous aadmi tha yaar!
I think apni ek dosti fluids me ho gayi thi, outside of the Akarsh and Bhatia and gang - a real library friendship with I think was very very nice. Uske baad toh canteen me hi milte the zyada ya aakarsh ke room pe --- also room ka taala todne ke time xD
You're a very standup guy, no bullshit attitude. Poker nights pe milte rahenge!
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
Nachiiii mamaaaa! You may be literally the most striking human being ever man. Tune toh mere IITK life me chaar chand laga diye the bhai. More than two of my exes know you by name (and game) which trust me, is saying a lot. COVID life me bhi ab tune chaar chand laga diye hain bhai jaldi se karde kal hi karde bhai please time lagta hai thoda aane me. Hamari wing ka na ho ke bhi tu hamari wing ka tha bhai, Vedant ke double room me reh hi lena chahiye tha tujhe 3rd year me full time. Tu itna pav kaise kha leta hai?????? Kasol me toh tune kya kya dikha diya bhai mai kabhi nahi bhulunga wo Challal aur Katagla aur baaki random gaon. Freedom is truly hard to find but we found it lol :P
Nice man. Milte rahenge Amsterdam ki trip banani hai jaldi
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text: Cool, friendly, intelligent, and awesome. CSE IITK had amazing gems and you are definitely one of them. Always nonchalant and calm. Naman sir it has been a pleasure knowing you. Kaafi kaafi time beaten kari humne KD me aur CC wali canteen me aur Hall 3 ke raaste pe. Social circles alag hote hue bhi hum dono ache dost rahe hain bhai kaafi! Touch me rehna dost!
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text: Bansal Sir, you're rocking awesome. Everything perfectly balanced not too much not too little. Good optimization of what to do and what to leave, amazing management of time and coding, and leisure. Sorry we blew up Techkriti we were very naive then. XD
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
C110 Family <3

You, me, Kevlin were amazing roommates yaar, the best I could ever have asked for. You've taught me more than a few neat tricks ;) Thank you so much Vedant for all of the time we spent together - talking, discussing, debating, deciding. The only games I ever played at college were on your Laptop (RE4)! I will definitely come to Nagpur once we will meet at your farmhouse or your country club wherever you're taking me. ALsoooo your "squad assemble" should happen soon :P "Bhai iss sem class jaana" 
Kevlin will definitely be the first of us to get married so lets use that opportunity for some more craZ shit!
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
Vineet Sir Shukla! We've never once in 4 years seen eye to eye on things but you're a pretty okay chap! Wing hangouts, wing bulla(s) are all we've really done. I think it's very good though that you're the kind of person who likes to have their own INFORMED opinion on things. First year me thoda zyada tang kardiya tha tujhe uske liye sorry, you just come off as the sort of guy jiski lene me maza aayega - evident from the fact that kisi ke bhi birthday pe teri GPL ho hi jaati thi xD
Have fun man, do shit, and keep going on like you do.
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
Vipul bhai apan toh PE se ek dusre ko jaante hain (oh those BT days). CSE assignments, random ass chilling have been fun. Our 5cr conversation was nice ;) utna toh tu pahuch hi jayega startup karke, aur aage ka soch bhai ab! Also tere kya sahi principles hain yaar mujhe toh laga tha bend karwa dunga tune nahi maana par, good to see people still like ot stick to their principles, because I have come to think that they're a bitch.
Have fun man, we'll keep in touch for sure!
Remember me for your next startup, kothari boy is in your corner!

Praveen becho!!!! Isse achi shuruaat nhi mil skti thi. Icebreaker toh tune sameer ke birthday pr poori wing ko diya tha, usse hi baat nhi kr pya. Thank you bol de teri antaragini mein photo le li tih saath mein. Baki mst bada toh hai tu, bs thoda khel leta jyada toh shyd km sunta hum logon se. I know tera interest hai android aur games development mein, aur bhot achi bhi krta hai bhai lge rhna. Tere se bnwana hai future mein, paise nhi milenge LOL. Aur thoda logon se interact kiya kr, nhi toh kuch nhi hone wla tera. Aur haan thodi english sudhar le, nhi toh japanese seekhni pd jygi. Tere chate hi shyd apna photoshoot poora ho pya, nhi toh shyd hi hota. Teri train krwa kr kya hi mza aaya bhai. kabhi free ho toh call kr liya kr.
PS: Shaadi mein jrur bulana, I know teri jld hone wli hai.
author: Ritesh  Kumar

text: Bhai kahan se shuru krun. Tereko shyd yaad na ho , pehli baar tu mila tha jb tu E-Cell ke event ke liye sbko bulane aaya tha. Phir ek do br tere room pe mila, kya safai rkhta tha bhai tu. First summers se toh bhai saath  hi rhe. Woh summer kya epic tha. Mai bahar jyada nhi jta tha, isliye saath bhot photos nhi hai yr, but memories bhot hein. Hr course se related itni hein ki kya btaun. Baswana sir wla toh yaad hi hoga.OS yaad hai tu roj uthane aata tha aur hum soe reh jte the.  Last year maien socha tha yr ghumenge pr kya hi ho gya. Phir bhi last mein tum logon ne saare mze krwa hi diye. Bhot ache din the yr, yeah akhiri ke 1-2 mahine campus mein.  Ek GOA trip krni hai bhai saath mein, jb bhi time mile. Tere aur tere bhai mein pehchana mushkil h bhai. Jld hi milte hein yr.  All the best!!!
